   NEW YORK -- Pearson PLC's Penguin USA named two executives
to the top editorial posts at its principal hardcover and
paperback divisions.
   Al Silverman, a vice president and contributing editor of
Penguin USA, was named publisher and editor in chief of the
Viking division, which publishes hardcovers. Mr. Silverman,
65 years old, was chairman and chief executive officer of
Time Warner Inc.'s Book of the Month Club before joining
Penguin in 1989.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Silverman succeeds Christine Pevitt, who resigned in
June. Ms. Pevitt presided over both the hardcover and
paperback divisions, but those duties have now been split.
