syringe he had used to give the tiny penguins breakfast.;    "A nice chap went
out and found some fresh squid and shrimp, then persuaded a barman here at the
airport to liquidize it for me.";    Last month Hill flew to Chile, then on to
the Falklands, where he set out for his egg-hunting grounds aboard a Danish
icebreaker.;    Returning to Santiago with the eggs, Hill found heavy airport
security. "The incubators should have been kept in a cool area at the airport,
