<HEAD>50 Penguins Found Dead in Hold of Taiwanese Trawler</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAPE TOWN, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The bodies of 50 endangered
penguins were found floating in the flooded hold of a Taiwanese
fishing trawler that ran aground, environmental officials said.
   The carcasses of the Jackass penguins had been individually
packaged in plastic bags, the officials said Friday.
   The fishing trawler An Hung ran aground on the rocky
southwestern coast of South Africa early Tuesday, and 15
crewmembers were rescued by helicopter. One was found dead on the
beach Tuesday.
   The Jackass penguin is unique to the southern African coast and
is protected under South African law. Its population has diminished
after centuries of being hunted.
   Its natural habitat has been diminished by fishing and the
collection of the guano the bird uses to build its nests.
</TEXT>
