<TEXT>     "These are kind of mystery birds," said Jay Holcomb, the director of
International Bird Rescue in Berkeley, which is caring for about 100 of the
birds. "We don't know where they're coming from.";    The birds -- known as
common murres -- nest on the Farallon Islands. They resemble miniature
penguins, with black and white coloring.;    Authorities had no immediate
estimate of how many of the birds were dead and how many alive. Holcomb,
however, estimated that about 20 to 25 birds had washed ashore daily since
